A dedicated television station for toddlers and parents, Baby TV, has made its debut on cable TV platform, StarTimes. The globally acclaimed TV station is filled with series of stories, songs, rhymes, and loveable characters for the viewing pleasure of toddlers and their parents. As it made its debut on StarTimes in March 2020, Baby TV has rolled out some of the programmes expected to thrill toddlers, kids and parents. Some of the programmes include ‘Tutti Frutti,’ a musical series, ‘Rocco,’ the story around a squirrel’s challenges, ‘Teeny & Tiny’ and ‘Beep Beep,’ amongst others. ‘Baby TV’ joined the 14 new channels promised by StarTimes after a recent upgrade across Africa at no extra cost.